# pnpm strict mode (the default) puts each package in its own isolated
# directory. libsodium-wrappers-sumo imports `./libsodium-sumo.mjs` via a
# relative path inside its own dist directory — but the libsodium-sumo
# package lives in a sibling package directory under .pnpm, so the relative
# import 404s and any module that transitively pulls libsodium (most of
# @meshsdk/core's wallet code) fails at load time.
#
# Hoist libsodium-* into the workspace's top-level node_modules so the
# relative import resolves. This is the standard mesh-on-pnpm workaround
# (mesh's docs reference it for the same symptom).
public-hoist-pattern[]=*libsodium*
